# Root build context is used by the Next app images (apps/storefront|admin/Dockerfile, context=repo
# root — they need pnpm-workspace + packages/*). Ship only what `pnpm install` + `next build` need:
# workspace manifests, lockfile, shared config, and app/package SOURCE. Everything installed or built
# is regenerated in-image. (core-api uses its own context services/core-api + its own .dockerignore,
# so excluding services/ here is safe for the Next builds.)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/*.tsbuildinfo
**/.turbo
**/coverage
**/test-results
.git
.github
.claude
docs
designs
services
*.md
# Never let a real secret into the build context (keep the template).
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
